<TITLE> Fakhruddin stresses deeper communication among advisers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 28 (bdnews24.com) -- Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed Saturday advised advisers, secretaries and other officials to increase formal and informal communication to bring more dynamism to the administration, a spokesman said. Fakhruddin emphasised that round-the-clock communication would speed up work, the chief adviser's press secretary Syed Fahim Munaim told bdnews24.com by phone after a cabinet meeting at the CAO. The council of advisers discussed reform at different levels of the administration to add speed to work. Saturday's meeting was meant to reflect on the progress of work by the emergency government. "The chief adviser expressed satisfaction with the progress of work. He gave advice for deeper communication," Munaim said. Fakhruddin said the old rules of different ministries have to be amended and the quality of services must be ensured for people. The cabinet told the meeting that service providers have to make a citizen's charter and publicise it among people to ensure the quality of services. Officials familiar with the details of the meeting said the advisory council held 40 meetings in the first six months after the emergency government took office in mid-January. The meetings took decisions on 205 issues115 of them were implemented. Efforts are on to implement 90 other decisions, according to the details of the meeting. In the same period, the council of advisers gave final approval to 14 ordinancesnine of them came into effect and the rest are in the process of execution. Seven permanent and two temporary committees of the advisory council were formed. The committees held 41 meetings. bdnews24.c
